 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 be a ring.
 We say 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 is 
\series bold
antilocal 
\series default
if it satisfies the following property: for all units 
\begin_inset Formula $u$
\end_inset

 of 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

, either 
\begin_inset Formula $1+u=0$
\end_inset

 or 
\begin_inset Formula $1+u$
\end_inset

 is a unit.
 
