 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 be an antilocal ring.
 Then 
\begin_inset Formula $\Bbbk:=A^{\times}\cup\{0\}$
\end_inset

 is a field.
 Moreover, 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 is a reduced 
\begin_inset Formula $\Bbbk$
\end_inset

-algebra with 
\begin_inset Formula $\Bbbk$
\end_inset

 being the largest field contained in 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

.
 
